                    "value": "<p>The ruin collapses up to three 10-footby- 10-foot sections of its ceiling. The ruin takes [[/r 10 # damage]] damage per section it collapses, and it can't collapse the same section until it has been repaired. Each creature in one of these areas takes [[/r 8d10 # bludgeoning damage]] bludgeoning damage with a <span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"35\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Collapse Ceiling DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save. On a failed save, the creature is also restrained under the rubble until it Escapes (DC 33).</p>"
